msgstr "お支払いを確認し、さまざまな条件を比較してください。"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:241
msgid "How is my monthly payment calculated?"
msgstr "毎月の支払いはどのように計算されますか?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:247
msgid ""
"Monthly payments are calculated using the standard amortization formula: M ="
" P[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1], where P is principal, r is monthly rate, and n is "
"number of payments."
msgstr ""
"月々の支払いは、標準的な償却式 M = P[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1] を使用して計算されます。ここで、P は元本、r は月々の金利、n"
" は支払い回数です。"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:253
msgid "Should I choose a shorter or longer term?"
msgstr "短期または長期の期間を選択する必要がありますか?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:259
msgid ""
"Shorter terms mean higher monthly payments but less total interest. Longer "
"terms lower your monthly payment but cost more over time. Choose based on "
"your budget and goals."
msgstr ""
"期間が短いと月々の支払額は高くなりますが、総利息は少なくなります。契約期間が長くなると月々の支払い額は減りますが、長期的には費用が高くなります。予算や目的に応じてお選びください。"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:265
msgid "What's the benefit of biweekly payments?"
msgstr "隔週支払いのメリットは何ですか?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:271
msgid ""
"Paying half your monthly payment every two weeks results in 26 half-payments"
" (13 full payments) per year instead of 12. This extra payment goes to "
"principal, saving interest and time."
msgstr ""
"月々の支払いの半分を 2 週間ごとに支払うと、年間 12 回ではなく 26 回の半額支払い (13 回の全額支払い) "
"になります。この余分な支払いは元本に充当されるため、利息と時間を節約できます。"

