#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:725
msgid "Understanding Calculation Modes"
msgstr "計算モードについて"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:728
msgid "Room Size Mode"
msgstr "部屋サイズモード"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:730
msgid ""
"Calculate BTU from length, width, and height measurements. Best for new "
"construction, room planning, or when you have complete dimensional "
"information. Provides both area and volume calculations."
msgstr ""
"長さ、幅、高さの測定値から BTU を計算します。新築、間取り計画、または完全な寸法情報がある場合に最適です。面積と体積の両方の計算を提供します。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:734
msgid "Area BTU Mode"
msgstr "エリアBTUモード"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:736
msgid ""
"Calculate BTU from total area when you know the square footage but not "
"individual dimensions. Useful for existing spaces where you've measured the "
"floor area but don't need volume calculations."
msgstr ""
"平方フィートはわかっているが、個々の寸法がわからない場合は、総面積から BTU "
"を計算します。床面積は測定済みだが体積計算は必要ない既存のスペースに便利です。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:740
msgid "Unit Conversion Mode"
msgstr "単位変換モード"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:742
msgid ""
"Convert between BTU and other energy units (kWh, Joules, Calories, Foot-"
"Pounds). Useful for comparing energy consumption, understanding utility "
"bills, or converting between different energy measurement systems."
msgstr ""
"BTU と他のエネルギー単位 (kWh、ジュール、カロリー、フィートポンド) "
"の間で変換します。エネルギー消費量の比較、公共料金の把握、または異なるエネルギー測定システム間の変換に役立ちます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:746
msgid "Cooling Load Mode"
msgstr "冷却負荷モード"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:748
msgid ""
"Calculate comprehensive cooling requirements including base load, window "
"heat gain (1000 BTU per window), occupant heat (400 BTU per person), and "
"appliance heat. Essential for accurate air conditioning system sizing."
msgstr ""
"ベース負荷、窓の熱利得 (窓あたり 1000 BTU)、占有者の熱 (1 人あたり 400 "
"BTU)、および機器の熱を含む包括的な冷却要件を計算します。空調システムの正確なサイジングに不可欠です。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:761
msgid ""
"The main result showing the total BTU capacity needed for your space. This "
"is the number you'll use when selecting HVAC equipment. Most systems are "
"rated in BTU/hour, so this value represents the hourly capacity requirement."
msgstr ""
"スペースに必要な合計 BTU 容量を示す主な結果。これは、HVAC 機器を選択するときに使用する番号です。ほとんどのシステムは "
"BTU/時間で評価されるため、この値は時間当たりの容量要件を表します。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:767
msgid ""
"Shows your BTU requirement converted to other energy units: kilowatt-hours "
"(kWh), Joules, Calories, and Foot-Pounds. Useful for comparing with "
"electrical consumption, understanding energy costs, or international unit "
"conversions."
msgstr ""
"BTU 要件を他のエネルギー単位 (キロワット時 (kWh)、ジュール、カロリー、フィートポンド) "
"に変換して表示します。電力消費量との比較、エネルギーコストの理解、または国際単位換算に役立ちます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:773
msgid ""
"Breaks down the calculation showing area, volume (if applicable), base BTU, "
"and the multipliers applied for insulation and climate. This helps you "
"understand how each factor affects the final requirement."
msgstr ""
"面積、体積（該当する場合）、基本 "
"BTU、および断熱材と気候に適用される乗数を示す計算の内訳。これは、各要素が最終要件にどのような影響を与えるかを理解するのに役立ちます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:779
msgid ""
"Provides a detailed walkthrough of the calculation process, showing "
"dimension conversions, area/volume calculations, base BTU determination, "
"multiplier applications, and final BTU calculation. This transparency helps "
"verify accuracy and understand the methodology."
msgstr ""
"寸法の変​​換、面積/体積の計算、基本 BTU の決定、乗算器の適用、および最終的な BTU "
"計算を示す、計算プロセスの詳細なウォークスルーを提供します。この透明性は、精度を検証し、方法論を理解するのに役立ちます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:783
msgid "Interactive Charts"
msgstr "インタラクティブなチャート"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:785
msgid ""
"Visual representations include energy units comparison (bar chart), BTU "
"gauge (doughnut chart showing required vs remaining capacity), and cooling "
"load breakdown (for cooling calculations). These charts help visualize the "
"data and understand proportions."
msgstr ""
"視覚的な表現には、エネルギー単位の比較 (棒グラフ)、BTU ゲージ (必要な容量と残りの容量を示すドーナツ チャート)、および冷却負荷の内訳 "
"(冷却計算用) が含まれます。これらのグラフは、データを視覚化し、比率を理解するのに役立ちます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:795
msgid ""
"Understanding energy unit conversions helps compare HVAC energy consumption "
"with other energy uses. Here are the key conversion factors:"
msgstr "エネルギー単位の変換を理解すると、HVAC のエネルギー消費と他のエネルギー使用を比較するのに役立ちます。主な変換要因は次のとおりです。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:802
msgid "BTU Equivalent"
msgstr "相当する BTU"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:803
msgid "Common Use"
msgstr "共通使用"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:810
msgid "HVAC systems, heating/cooling"
msgstr "HVAC システム、暖房/冷房"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:815
msgid "Electrical energy, utility bills"
msgstr "電気エネルギー、公共料金"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:820
msgid "Scientific measurements, SI unit"
msgstr "科学測定、SI単位"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:825
msgid "Food energy, nutrition"
msgstr "食物エネルギー、栄養"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:830
msgid "Mechanical work, torque"
msgstr "機械的仕事、トルク"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:845
msgid ""
"These calculations are estimates based on standard formulas and industry "
"guidelines. Actual requirements may vary based on specific building "
"characteristics, local climate variations, window orientation, ceiling "
"height, and other factors."
msgstr ""
"これらの計算は、標準の計算式と業界のガイドラインに基づいた推定値です。実際の要件は、特定の建物の特性、地域の気候変動、窓の向き、天井の高さ、その他の要因によって異なる場合があります。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:851
msgid ""
"For accurate HVAC system sizing, especially for new construction or major "
"renovations, consult with a licensed HVAC contractor or engineer. They can "
"perform Manual J calculations (industry standard) that account for all "
"factors."
msgstr ""
"特に新築や大規模改修の場合、HVAC システムの正確なサイジングについては、認可を受けた HVAC "
"請負業者またはエンジニアにご相談ください。すべての要素を考慮した手動 J 計算 (業界標準) を実行できます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:857
msgid ""
"Consider factors like ceiling height (standard is 8 feet, but vaulted "
"ceilings need more BTU), window orientation (south-facing windows get more "
"sun), number and size of windows, and local building codes when making final"
" decisions."
msgstr ""
"最終的な決定を下す際には、天井の高さ (標準は 8 フィートですが、アーチ型天井にはより多くの BTU が必要です)、窓の向き "
"(南向きの窓の方が日当たりが良くなります)、窓の数とサイズ、地域の建築基準法などの要素を考慮してください。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:863
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Add 10-20%% extra capacity for safety margin, future expansion, or if your "
"home has unusual features. However, avoid oversizing by more than 20%% as it"
" can cause short-cycling, poor humidity control, and energy waste."
msgstr ""
"安全マージン、将来の拡張、またはご自宅に特殊な機能がある場合に備えて、10 ～ 20%% "
"の追加容量を追加します。ただし、サイクルが短く、湿度制御が不十分で、エネルギーの無駄が発生する可能性があるため、20%% "
"を超えるオーバーサイズは避けてください。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:869
msgid ""
"Energy efficiency improvements (better insulation, energy-efficient windows,"
" sealing air leaks) can significantly reduce BTU requirements and lower "
"energy costs. Consider these improvements before sizing your HVAC system."
msgstr ""
"エネルギー効率の改善 (断熱性の向上、エネルギー効率の高い窓、空気漏れの密閉) により、BTU 要件が大幅に削減され、エネルギー コストが削減されます。"
" HVAC システムのサイズを決定する前に、これらの改善点を検討してください。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:879
msgid "How many BTU do I need per square foot?"
msgstr "平方フィートあたり何 BTU 必要ですか?"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:880
msgid ""
"The standard is approximately 20 BTU per square foot, but this varies from "
"15-30 BTU/sq ft based on room type. Kitchens and attics need more (30), "
"while bathrooms need less (15). Our calculator automatically adjusts based "
"on your room type selection."
msgstr ""
"標準は 1 平方フィートあたり約 20 BTU ですが、これは部屋のタイプに応じて 15 ～ 30 "
"BTU/平方フィートの間で異なります。キッチンと屋根裏部屋にはさらに多く (30) 必要ですが、バスルームにはそれほど必要ありません "
"(15)。当社の計算機は、選択した部屋タイプに基づいて自動的に調整します。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:883
msgid "What's the difference between heating and cooling BTU?"
msgstr "加熱BTUと冷却BTUの違いは何ですか?"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:884
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Cooling typically requires 20%% more BTU than heating because air "
"conditioning must remove both heat and humidity. The cooling load mode "
"accounts for additional factors like solar heat gain, occupants, and "
"appliances that primarily affect cooling needs."
msgstr ""
"空調は熱と湿気の両方を除去する必要があるため、通常、冷房には暖房より 20%% 多くの BTU "
"が必要です。冷房負荷モードでは、主に冷房のニーズに影響を与える太陽熱取得、居住者、機器などの追加要因が考慮されます。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:887
msgid "How does insulation affect BTU requirements?"
msgstr "絶縁はBTU要件にどのような影響を与えますか?"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:888
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Insulation quality has a significant impact. Excellent insulation can reduce"
" BTU needs by 20%%, while poor or no insulation can increase requirements by"
" 50-100%%. Proper insulation is one of the most cost-effective ways to "
"reduce HVAC requirements."
msgstr ""
"断熱材の品質は大きな影響を与えます。優れた断熱材では BTU の必要性が 20%% 削減されますが、断熱材が不十分または断熱材がない場合は、要件が 50"
" ～ 100%% 増加する可能性があります。適切な断熱は、HVAC 要件を削減する最もコスト効率の高い方法の 1 つです。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:891
msgid "Should I size my system larger than calculated?"
msgstr "システムのサイズを計算より大きくする必要がありますか?"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:892
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Add 10-20%% for safety margin, but avoid oversizing by more than 20%%. "
"Oversized systems short-cycle (turn on/off frequently), which reduces "
"efficiency, causes poor humidity control, and increases wear. Proper sizing "
"is more important than extra capacity."
msgstr ""
"安全マージンとして 10 ～ 20%% を追加しますが、20%% "
"を超えるオーバーサイズは避けてください。大型のシステムはサイクルが短く（頻繁にオン/オフする）、効率が低下し、湿度制御が不十分になり、摩耗が増加します。適切なサイジングは追加容量よりも重要です。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:895
msgid "How do I convert BTU to tons for air conditioning?"
msgstr "空調用に BTU をトンに変換するにはどうすればよいですか?"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:896
msgid ""
"1 ton of cooling = 12,000 BTU/hour. To convert, divide BTU by 12,000. For "
"example, 24,000 BTU = 2 tons. Most residential air conditioners are rated in"
" tons (1.5, 2, 2.5, 3, 4, 5 tons)."
msgstr ""
"1 トンの冷却 = 12,000 BTU/時間。変換するには、BTU を 12,000 で割ります。たとえば、24,000 BTU = 2 "
"トンです。ほとんどの家庭用エアコンの定格はトン (1.5、2、2.5、3、4、5 トン) です。"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:899
msgid "What is Manual J calculation?"
msgstr "マニュアルJ計算とは何ですか？"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/btu_calculator.html:900
msgid ""
"Manual J is the industry-standard method for calculating heating and cooling"
" loads. It's more detailed than our calculator, accounting for every window,"
" door, wall, and building component. For new construction or major projects,"
" a professional Manual J calculation is recommended."
msgstr ""
"マニュアル J "
"は、冷暖房負荷を計算するための業界標準の方法です。これは、すべての窓、ドア、壁、建物のコンポーネントを考慮した計算機よりも詳細です。新築または大規模プロジェクトの場合は、専門的なマニュアル"
" J 計算をお勧めします。"

